                <h1 class="title">Getting started</h1>

                <p class='brief'>Well, it's pretty simple. Just follow the examples included on the following tips:</p>
                
                 <h4 class="title">Controllers</h4>
                 <p class='brief'>All controllers should extend the main controller. The main controller is responsible to instance some features like request/response and views. <br /> Just follow the home controller example.</p>
                 <h4 class="title">Routes</h4>
                 <p class='brief'>You can add more routes into core/routes.php file. Just follow the examples there. You can also set a uri like users/{id} to pass a param 'id' to your controller. <br />Yeah, awesome.</p>
                 <h4 class="title">Templates</h4>
                 <p class='brief'>Templates are placed into src/views folder. They are twig templates. You can learn twig -> <a href="http://twig.sensiolabs.org/documentation">here</a> <-</p>
                 <h4 class="title">Cache</h4>
                 <p class='brief'>Cache makes things faster. But they can be annoying as you develop and can't see the changes. If it happens, just delete the contents inside the /cache/ folder. Don't blame me, I am trying to help you.</p>
                
